## MISSION STATEMENT
Create an interactive visual encyclopedia showing connections between violinists, their teachers, instrument makers, and historical events through an intuitive interface adapted for children and researchers.

## CORE PRINCIPLES
- Zero-backend architecture: All data stored in JSON/YAML files in repository
- Mobile-first design: Full adaptation for all devices and screen orientations
- Vector graphics: SVG shapes instead of raster images for scalability
- Security first: Multi-level protection for admin panel and data
- Open source: MIT license with full transparency
- Accessibility: WCAG 2.1 AA compliance for users with disabilities

